Thirty-four members of a wedding party drowned  when an overloaded boat sank in the southern Indian district of Bellary, the  Press Trust of India (PTI) reported Tuesday.
Ten others survived the capsize in the Tungabhadra river late Monday by  swimming to safety, the news agency said.
All but three of the victims were women and children.
Meanwhile, a speeding bus carrying a wedding party crashed in the district  of Buldana near Bombay late Monday, killing the bridegroom and five other  people, PTI said in a separate dispatch. Twenty-three were injured.
